    {
        "content": "<p>tschneidereit opened <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/pull/13839\">PR #13839</a> from <code>tschneidereit:epoch-perf</code> to <code>bytecodealliance:main</code>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Setting the initial epoch deadline to <code>1</code> instead of the default <code>0</code> means that the deadline check doesn't immediately trigger. In local testing, this essentially eliminates the performance difference between <code>wasmtime serve</code> and <code>wasmtime serve -W timeout=1</code> for a Rust Hello World WASIp2 component. In absolute terms, that means it goes from about 120k RPS to 155k RPS.</p>\n</blockquote>",
